org.ow2.proactive.resourcemanager.common.event

Class RMNodeSourceEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.ow2.proactive.resourcemanager.common.event.RMEvent
      • org.ow2.proactive.resourcemanager.common.event.RMNodeSourceEvent
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, Comparable<RMEvent>

    @PublicAPI
public class RMNodeSourceEvent
extends RMEvent
    This class implements the Event object related to a NodeSource.

    This event objects is thrown to all Resource Manager Monitors to inform them about a NodeSource event. Events can be:

    • new NodeSource added to the RMCore
    • the NodeSource removed from the RMCore
    A node source has to aspects in a Monitor's point of view a name, its sourceID. NodeSource types are defined in RMConstants.
    Since:
    ProActive Scheduling 0.9
    See Also:
    RMMonitoring, Serialized Form
